# Gaelic Brie

> Inspired by an appetizer once served at McLadden’s in Northampton, these toast points with Brie, balsamic drizzle, and arugula are big on flavor. #app

Preheat the oven to 400 degrees.

- French Bread |  | 

Cut French bread into 1/2” thick slices on the bias and arrange on a baking sheet.

- Olive Oil |  | 
- Salt |  | 

Lightly brush tops of each piece with olive oil and sprinkle with salt.

Place in the oven for 10-15 minutes.

- Garlic | 1 clove, whole | 

Once browned, allow the pieces to cool before rubbing in a whole garlic clove.

> At this point, you can stop and wait up to 24 hours before continuing.

- Brie |  | 

Place a slice of Brie on each piece and warm in the oven for 8-10 minutes.

- Arugula |  | 

Drizzle with balsamic glaze and arrange on a plate of arugula.

Place a few sprigs of arugula on each bite as you go!

